                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.C1199/275: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul at Geneva</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gilbert</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-06-22T16:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 22, 1937—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>108. For Grady. Your 228, June 21, 3 p.m. It is regretted that it would be
                    contrary to the Department’s policy to permit an official of the State
                    Department to serve as substitute for you.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
